LLMs settings - 
1. temperature - if set temperature to low, it reduces randomness, so more deterministic answer, good for maths and factual accuracy.higher temperature make smodel creative and diverse in response.
2. max tokens  - maximum number of tokens model can genearte. lower tokens   -helpful to get shorter response, like summarizing, large token helpful when writing articles.
3. stop sequences - tell llm to stop genearting text once they are encountered. 
4. top p - if value 1 means considered all possible tokens while generating response, but if 0.5 - it means considered only 50 % of tokens while genarting responses.
5. frequency penalty - discourages repeted words
6. Presence penalty - Encourages the introduction of new topics.

