what are small language model? (SLMs)
Small Language Models (SLMs), highlighting their compactness and efficiency compared to larger language models. . they are smaller, more efficinet, scaled down versions of LLMs.
SLMs may lack the extensive capabilities of models like ChatGPT-4 or Gemini, they still perform essential tasks such as text generation and language understanding with significantly fewer parameters.
they are faster, cheaper and more effiecint to run (lesser computational requirements, optimized for speed and lower resource consumption).
Comparison with Large Models: For example, ChatGPT-4 has 170 trillion parameters, while SLMs like Google Gamma and Llama 3 operate with just a few billion parameters.
Practical Use Cases:
Edge Computing/IoT devices: SLMs are suitable for smart devices and IoT applications due to their low resource requirements.
Mobile Applications: They enhance real-time interactions in mobile apps, providing a better user experience.
Customer Support: SLMs efficiently manage predefined queries in chatbots without the need for complex large models.
Offline Applications: They can power personal assistants on smartphones, ensuring privacy by processing data locally. they can still provide recommneadyioons, without connecting to cloud.


